title: KYLIN_HOME will be confused when multiple tomcat instances are deployed on the same machine node
body: KYLIN_HOME will be confused when multiple tomcat instances are deployed on the same machine  node, if we just set one KYLIN_HOME for global use on that machine, the multiple tomcats will not find the path directly, thus we set the KYLIN_HOME side kylin.sh, and this KYLIN_HOME's scope is only inside the kylin.sh and its derived scripts. In addition, we can still set a KYLIN_HOME for global use on that machine.

title: support specifying different kylin_job_conf.xml(isolation of hadoop job queues) for different kylin projects
body:
1, https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KYLIN-1241, for one hadoop cluster, we sometimes want to assign different hadoop job queues(machine resources) for different kylin projects(different business group), thus, adding logic to auto detect the kylin_job_conf_medium/small/large_projectname.xml first, then kylin_job_conf_projectname.xml, then kylin_job_conf_medium/small/large.xml, finally kylin_job_conf.xml, if still not found, throws an exception. It means we can support project level kylin job configuration file for different projects. and the piece of codes have been tested by my self with building cubes, refreshing cubes, and etc, which works successfully.

2, https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KYLIN-1242, commit 'ead10dc' is for the case that when users are in China mainland, we may be blocked with some download urls, therefore, we cannot build the front end just one time, it is possible for us to try many times to build the front end without building the back end again and again, so, for the script/build.sh, I added a special check, when running: sh build.sh fe, it builds the front end only, when running: sh build.sh be, it builds the back end only, when running: sh build.sh, it builds both the fe and be components.

title: support specifying different kylin_job_conf.xml(isolation of hadoop job queues) for different kylin projects
body:
1. for one hadoop cluster, we sometimes want to assign different hadoop job queues(machine resources) for different kylin projects(different business group), thus, adding logic to auto detect the kylin_job_conf_medium/small/large_projectname.xml first, then kylin_job_conf_projectname.xml, then kylin_job_conf_medium/small/large.xml, finally kylin_job_conf.xml, if still not found, throws an exception. It means we can support project level kylin job configuration file for different projects. and the piece of codes have been tested by my self with building cubes, refreshing cubes, and etc, which works successfully.
2. currently, commit 'ead10dc' is for the case that when users are in China mainland, we may be blocked with some download urls, therefore, we cannot build the front end just one time, it is possible for us to try many times to build the front end without building the back end again and again, so, for the script/build.sh, I added a special check, when running: sh build.sh fe, it builds the front end only, when running: sh build.sh be, it builds the back end only, when running: sh build.sh, it builds both the fe and be components.

title: KYLIN-752 improve query performance for values that are not in dictio
body:
A quick fix to drop the not-in-dictionary values before generating hbase scan range.
And based on it, we can make a further optimization that as long as there is at least one andFilter is empty(after we drop the not-in-dictionary values), we can simply assert that the whole andFilters is empty to avoid an unnecessary hbase scan.
However, this strategy only works for 'EQ', 'IN'. For 'LT', 'LTE', 'GT', 'GTE', we have to replace them with the some sort of closest smaller or bigger values by calling "final public int getIdFromValue(T value, int roundingFlag)" of "Dictionary" class.
